</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/ubelmonte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belmonte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The King</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#939393>(1/23/01 2:17:38 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/sstearns78/Images/Destiny02.jpg width=140 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Experience Spots</span><hr size=1> Some notes on the sisters....from my experience.<br>
<br>
1) Bring a partner: Until you're 14 or 15... you'll need at least a partner. Like Syzian said... they aggro... from far away. They also hit pretty durned hard for their level.<br>
<br>
2) Bring a ton of containers: Toolboxes preferred (can hold anything, only weigh 0.4). Purity Belts are a 95% drop. Worth roughly 1.5pp to DEs in Neriak.<br>
<br>
3) Don't bother with the halbards: Almost every Sister will be wielding a rusty halberd. Destroy 'em. The selling value of it is not worth the weight.<br>
<br>
